<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="intmin">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>intmin</refname>
        <refpurpose>smallest integer that can be represented by integer type</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
            y = intmin(x)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>x</term>
            <listitem>
                <para>integer matrix or string.</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>y</term>
            <listitem>
                <para>integer scalar.</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            Returns the smallest integer that can be represented for a given integer type specifed by <term>x</term>.
        </para>
        <para>
            <term>x</term> might be a single string designating an integer type, i.e.'int8', ...,
            'int64', 'uint8', ..., 'uint64' (cf. <function>typeof</function>), 
            or a variable or value of an integer type.
        </para>
        <para>
            The result <term>y</term> is a scalar integer of the type specified by <term>x</term>.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// smallest integer representable by 'uint64'
intmin('uint64')

// smallest integer representable by 'int32'
x=int32(123)
intmin(x) // here only the type of 'x' matters, not the value!
 ]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="see also">
        <title>See also</title>
        <simplelist type="inline">
            <member>
                <link linkend="intmax">intmax</link>
            </member>
